  clusterroles
  roles
  priorityclasses --> pc
  csidrivers
  csinodes

Flags:
  -o wide/yaml   List information about a resource with more details
  -A             (used with ex. 'kubectl get all -A') - more information
  -w             Wait - give updating output as changes are made
  -f             Specify file name
  -L             Add a column where at the top we have the key of the label
  --all          all used for ex. delete pods --all
  --sort-by='.metadata.creationTimestamp'      To order events by creationTimestamp
  --type
  --name
  --port
  --targetport
  --nodeport

Logs:
  kubectl logs <POD_NAME>          Show logs of the first listed container in the config of this pod
  -c <CONTAINER_NAME>              Specify a container to show the logs for
  --all-containers                 Show logs for all containers
  -f                               Show a stream
  --since 10s                      Show logs from last 10sec
